---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CaseStudySection from "../../layouts/CaseStudySection.astro";
import CaseStudyHero from "../../components/CaseStudyHero.astro";
import TableOfContents from "../../components/TableOfContents.astro";
import NextCaseStudy from "../../components/NextCaseStudy.astro";

const sectionNames = ["Context", "End Product", "Research", "Decisions", "Reflection"];
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <link rel="preload" href="/styles/case-studies.css" as="style" onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'">
    <noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/case-studies.css"></noscript>

    <script defer>
        // ensure the DOM is ready before querying
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const detailsElements = document.querySelectorAll('details');

            detailsElements.forEach(details => {
                details.addEventListener('toggle', () => {
                    if (!details.open) { // closed state
                        // scroll the summary (header) into view so users don't skip ahead
                        const summary = details.querySelector('summary');
                        if (summary) {
                            summary.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
                        } else {
                            details.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
                        }
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
</head>

<BaseLayout title="PRESS - The UCSD Guardian">
    <CaseStudyHero
        heroMediaUrl="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-hero"
        caseStudyTitle="Driving voter turnout for The UCSD Guardian’s student journalism referendum through a multi-touchpoint campaign"
        logisticItems={[
            ["Design Lead"],
            ["Executive Managers (2)", "Editorial (4)", "Marketing (2)", "Design (2)"],
             ["Content Design", "Copywriting", "Campaign Strategy", "Creative Direction"],
             ["4 weeks", "Mar. 2025 - Apr. 2025"]
        ]}
        ribbonOffset="translateY(-40%)"
        ribbonImageUrl="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/about/snowflake-3"
    />
    
    <main>
        <TableOfContents sectionNames={sectionNames}/>

        <div class="main-container">
            <CaseStudySection sectionName={sectionNames[0]} num={1}> <!--Context-->

                <article class="extra-space">
                    <h2>PRESS: Protect our Right to Express Student Stories</h2>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/intro-press.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        I collaborated with editorial leadership, product managers, and cross-functional teams at The UCSD Guardian to launch a multi-channel campaign for the PRESS referendum, with the goal of acquiring votes from at least 20% of the student body and reframing student journalism as a critical resource that’s at risk. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The campaign system I led helped:
                    </p>

                    <div class="insight gain-point">
                        <span>✅</span>
                        <p>
                            2x voter turnout compared to previous voting periods
                        </p>  
                    </div>

                    <div class="insight gain-point">
                        <span>✅</span>
                        <p>
                            Increased awareness and engagement with our coverage, especially into the next year
                        </p>  
                    </div>
                    <div class="insight gain-point">
                        <span>✅</span>
                        <p>
                             Reinforced the paper as an essential voice for students and SD communities
                        </p>  
                    </div>
                    
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space">
                    <p class="subtitle"> Problem </p>
                    <h3>
                        The UCSD Guardian was at risk of losing institutional funding, putting its ability to print and operate in jeopardy
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/guardian-at-risk.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        But the bigger issue wasn’t just funding. It was buy-in. Even though The Guardian this year made major strides in breaking critical stories on campus, the students who actively engaged were not the majority. Coverage existed, but it lived in the background: disconnected from students’ day-to-day.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <p class="subtitle">Stakes</p>
                    <h3>
                        If the referendum failed, the result wasn’t just one newspaper at risk of shutting down
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/without-the-guardian.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        It meant losing a central independent voice for student representation. And so this campaign was about preserving a shared source of truth for the student body.
                    </p>
                </article>

            </CaseStudySection>

            <CaseStudySection sectionName={sectionNames[1]} num={2}> <!-- End Product -->
                <h2>
                    How we successfully passed the 20% voter threshold without a budget
                </h2>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Solution #1 -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Solution</p>
                    <h3>
                        Turning awareness into a moment of action
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The campaign reframed student journalism as something to lose, not something in the background. By making the referendum feel immediate and consequential, students were more compelled to decide.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Before campaign -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Before the campaign</p>
                    <h4>
                        1000+ individuals & 30+ organizations signed in solidarity in the first 24 hours
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        In preparation for the campaign, The Guardian editorial board released a petition to gather community support and social proof in order to present to campus leadership. This early momentum validated student demand and established PRESS as a legitimate, campus-wide concern before outreach began.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article> <!-- During campaign -->
                    <p class="subtitle">During the campaign</p>
                    <h4>
                        Building a design system for clarity and urgency at scale
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        As Design Lead, I defined these design principles to guide the look/feel of our content design:
                    </p>
                    
                    <ul class="generic-ul">
                        <li>
                            <b>Scalable:</b> Key talking points and visual assets are easily reusable across platforms and contexts.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Practical:</b> Clear, plain language that helps students make confident decisions in voting.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Real stakes:</b> Lead with how students and campus life are affected.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </article>

                <article class="generic-container">
                    <div class="generic-container-margin-wrapper">
                        <div class="columns">
                            <figure>
                                <picture style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                                    <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-presenting101.webp">  -->
                                    <img style="margin-bottom: 0;" loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" data-src="/images/PRESS-feed-post-1.png">
                                </picture>
                                <figcaption>
                                    On-theme workshop to get people interested in storytelling and sharing to an audience.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>
                            <figure>
                                <picture style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                                    <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-presenting101.webp"> -->
                                    <img style="margin-bottom: 0;" loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" data-src="/images/PRESS-feed-post-3.png">
                                </picture>
                                <figcaption>
                                    On-theme workshop to get people interested in storytelling and sharing to an audience.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <!-- ============================================================= -->

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Solution #2 -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Solution</p>
                    <h3>
                        Designing for everywhere
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Visibility was key and needed to reach beyond our usual channels. The campaign lived across social, print, web, flyers, large campus displays, and more to ensure students encountered the campaign repeatedly in different contexts.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Design Decision #1 -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Design Decision</p>
                    <h3>
                        Making the message recognizable in seconds
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/press-message.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        Every asset was built around a repeatable call-to-action: Vote on PRESS. The focus was prioritizing key info for passersby at a glance - what was happening and what to do next.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article> <!-- Design Decision #2 -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Design Decision</p>
                    <h3>
                        Reintroducing who we were through distinct modes of engagement
                    </h3>
                </article>

                <article class="generic-container" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                    <div class="generic-container-margin-wrapper">
                        <div class="columns">
                            <figure>
                                <picture style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                                    <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-presenting101.webp">  -->
                                    <img style="margin-bottom: 0;" loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" data-src="/images/PRESS-feed-post-1.png">
                                </picture>
                                <figcaption>
                                    On-theme workshop to get people interested in storytelling and sharing to an audience.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>
                            <figure>
                                <picture style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                                    <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-presenting101.webp"> -->
                                    <img style="margin-bottom: 0;" loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" data-src="/images/workshop-writing-1.png">
                                </picture>
                                <figcaption>
                                    On-theme workshop to get people interested in storytelling and sharing to an audience.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>

                            <!--

                            <figure>
                                <video autoplay muted loop playsinline webkit-playsinline preload="none" width="100%">
                                    <source data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-announcement.mp4" type="video/mp4"/>
                                    <source data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-announcement.webm" type="video/webm"/>
                                </video>
                                <figcaption>
                                    Announcement post, how it works, and how to participate.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>

                            <figure>
                                <video autoplay muted loop playsinline webkit-playsinline preload="none" width="100%">
                                    <source data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-org-reveal.mp4" type="video/mp4"/>
                                    <source data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/maxmic-org-reveal.webm" type="video/webm"/>
                                </video>
                                <figcaption>
                                    Reveals partnering orgs, garnering substantial cross-traffic from reshares.
                                </figcaption>
                            </figure>
                            
                            -->
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        We split the Guardian’s campaign content into two buckets: one for visibility and voting, and the other is for editorial programming focused on community, transparency, and pre-professional workshops.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        This separation let us drive immediate action without losing the bigger picture, something to support now and be part of long-term.
                    </p>
                </article>
            </CaseStudySection>

            <CaseStudySection sectionName={sectionNames[2]} num={3}> <!-- Research -->
                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Voter turnout -->
                    <h2>
                        Where it all started
                    </h2>

                    <p class="subtitle">Research</p>
                    <h3>
                        Voter turnout at UCSD has been historically low
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/voter-threshold.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        One of the lowest of the UCs at just ~10% of the student body on average. In order to successfully pass our referendum, we needed roughly twice as many people.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space">
                    <h3>So why weren’t students turning out?</h3>
                    <p>
                        There are a multitude of factors that shape what campus engagement looks like at UCSD, ranging from its geography to accessibility to student government activities.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        But an even simpler answer was that students simply didn’t have a reason to invest their attention.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- U-Pass -->
                    <p class="subtitle">To see why, let’s see what worked in the past</p>
                    <h3>
                        U-Pass, 22,500 voters. Woah, what clicked this time around?
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/voter-u-pass-results.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        Breaking down the U-Pass referendum and similar initiatives, editorial and I found a few consistent patterns.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <p class="subtitle">Key Insights</p>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <h4>
                            Messaging was simple, repeatable, and action-oriented (“Vote on U-Pass”). 
                        </h4>

                        <h4>
                            Very clear why it directly affected students.
                        </h4>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <h4>
                            The call-to-action was reinforced from real people and sharing.
                        </h4>

                        <h4>
                            Campaigns showed up across multiple touchpoints, not just one. 
                        </h4>
                    </div>
                </article>
            </CaseStudySection>

            <CaseStudySection sectionName={sectionNames[3]} num={4}> <!--  Decisions -->
                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Copywriting-->
                    <h2>TODO: Heading</h2>
                    
                    <p class="subtitle">Copywriting</p>
                    <h3>
                        How do we distill what PRESS is about in just a few words?
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        With journalism, the concept of free press is highly contextual and carries different meanings from person-to-person. It takes more thought to convey its universal impact on students' lives. Contrast this with the U-Pass campaign, where the stakes were immediately clear to everyone: "Keep transit free."
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Ideation -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Ideation</p>
                    <h3>TODO: Heading</h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/copywriting-early-versions.png">
                    </picture>
                    <p>
                        In my early versions, the phrasing was either too abstract to ground viewers at a glance, or too long and didn’t roll off the tongue. They gestured at the cause, but failed to answer the basic questions: what is this, and why does it involve me?
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space">
                    <p class="subtitle">Constraint</p>
                    <h3>
                        University-owned displays required strictly neutral language
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        While we were allowed to make an argument in favor of PRESS on our own platforms, our core message needed to remain consistent everywhere, making it a challenge to find the right words without editorializing.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Final copy -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Final Iteration</p>
                    <h3>
                        A blank canvas that held its own across every touchpoint.
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/copywriting-final-base-anatomy.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        More detailed explanations could be found on social media and our dedicated PRESS page. But on its own, it effectively conveyed the <i>what, where, and when</i>.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <!-- ============================================================= -->

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Design Decisions -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Design Decisions</p>
                    <h3>
                        Responding to real-world feedback
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/reddit-guardian-ama.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        The Guardian’s PRESS AMA (Ask me Anything) on Reddit illustrated a clear pattern of students’ concerns. The most commonly asked questions related to how the funds were allocated. 
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Pain point -->
                    <h3>
                        With that, the most common point of confusion was also about the funds.
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/funding-allocation-before.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        Many assumed the Guardian would be receiving all the fees collected (~$440k). In reality, only ~$120k would directly support The Guardian’s operations.
                    </p>
                    <div class="insight pain-point">
                        <span>❌</span>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                The existing explanation on our website didn’t make this distinction clear, leaving students understandably unsure how funds were actually distributed.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article> <!-- Prioritization -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Prioritization</p>
                    <h3>
                        Focusing on clarity over completeness
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        We initially debated how much information to include, trying to answer every possible question and resolve all confusion. But as priorities shifted, executive helped us focus on what actually mattered—complementing the campaign’s core message.
                    </p>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/funding-allocation-after.png">
                    </picture>
                </article>

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Prioritized/Not prioritized -->
                    <span class="tag success">Prioritized</span>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h4>
                                Clarifying the total vs. actual allocation
                            </h4>
                            <p class="subtitle">
                                We focused on making it explicit that the Guardian does not receive the full amount, reducing the biggest source of skepticism upfront.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <picture>
                            <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/designlab/gentle-troubleshooting.webp"> -->
                            <img loading="lazy" alt="User asks a question using cursor chat to help troubleshoot viability of their idea." data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/improvement-ugc.png">
                        </picture>
                    </div>
                    <hr>
                    
                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h4>
                                Showing where the money we control goes
                            </h4>
                            <p class="subtitle">
                                Instead of overwhelming users with institutional language, we highlighted how Guardian-controlled funds support coverage, operations, and expand student opportunities.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <picture>
                            <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/designlab/gentle-troubleshooting.webp"> -->
                            <img loading="lazy" alt="User asks a question using cursor chat to help troubleshoot viability of their idea." data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/improvement-ugc.png">
                        </picture>
                    </div>
                    <hr>

                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h4>
                                Framing the ask as the minimum needed to operate
                            </h4>
                            <p class="subtitle">
                                We clarified that certain costs (like advisors or staff roles) were mandated, not discretionary, showing that part of the budget as a constraint we had to factor in.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <picture>
                            <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/designlab/gentle-troubleshooting.webp"> -->
                            <img loading="lazy" alt="User asks a question using cursor chat to help troubleshoot viability of their idea." data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/improvement-ugc.png">
                        </picture>
                    </div>
                    <hr>

                    <span class="tag negative">Not prioritized</span>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h4>
                                Exhaustive line-item breakdowns
                            </h4>
                            <p class="subtitle">
                                Breaking down every expense risked pulling users deeper into debate rather than helping them understand the overall structure.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <picture>
                            <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/designlab/gentle-troubleshooting.webp"> -->
                            <img loading="lazy" alt="User asks a question using cursor chat to help troubleshoot viability of their idea." data-src="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/improvement-ugc.png">
                        </picture>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <!-- ============================================================= -->

                <article class="extra-space"> <!-- Landing -->
                    <p class="subtitle">Revisiting Assumptions</p>
                    <h3>
                        Reconciling with a crucial gap in our campaign strategy
                    </h3>
                    
                    <p>
                        Moments like those prove why real-world feedback is invaluable. We assumed the biggest hurdle was the entry point. But the opposite happened: students easily understood the referendum at a glance, but some hesitated to act further when details felt unclear.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <p class="subtitle">Final Campaign System</p>
                    <h3>
                        So for the remainder of the campaign, we focused on removing friction at key decision points
                    </h3>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/user-journey-campaign-iteration-1.png">
                    </picture>
                    <picture>
                        <!-- <source type="image/webp" loading="lazy" data-srcset="https://media.dave-vo.com/file/dvfolio/maximalist-magazine/competitor-analysis-peer-orgs.webp"> -->
                        <img loading="lazy" alt="TODO ALT DESCRIPTION" src="/images/user-journey-campaign-iteration-2.png">
                    </picture>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        Students don’t engage with the campaign in the same way everywhere. Some would see it in passing, others want to seek more information. So we revisited each stage of the user journey to address people’s curiosities without overloading.
                    </p>
                </article>

            </CaseStudySection>

            <CaseStudySection sectionName={sectionNames[4]} num={5}> <!-- Reflection -->
                <h2>Debut to the max!</h2>
                <article class="extra-space">
                    <p class="subtitle">Impact</p>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h3>28K+</h3>
                            <p>
                                views on Instagram within 4 weeks
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div>
                            <h3>150+</h3>
                            <p>
                                attendees at first MaxMic
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div>
                            <h3>10+</h3>
                            <p>
                                partnerships with student organizations
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        MaxMic as a standalone event performed well, but it also had a sizable impact on the Maximalist brand itself. The momentum was able to carry into increased contributor interest to our zine issues, higher attendance to future events, as well as more invitations to table for other orgs.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <div class="reflection-unit" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);">
                        <span class="tag">If I had more time</span>
                        <h3>
                            Areas for improvement for future rollouts
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="columns">
                        <div>
                            <h4>
                                Encourage UGC
                            </h4>
                            <p class="subtitle">
                                Invite people to participate and build organic community prior to the event, prompting people to post something purple/orange, or share their talents in a maximalist spirit.
                            </p>
